.TH PASSPORT-UNLOCKER 1 "July 2026" "passport-unlocker 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
passport-unlocker \- list, inspect, and unlock compatible WD My Passport drives
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B passport-unlocker
.B list
.br
.B passport-unlocker
.B status
.BI --device-id " STABLE_ID"
.br
.B passport-unlocker
.B unlock
.BI --device-id " STABLE_ID"
.br
.B passport-unlocker
.B --version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B passport-unlocker
is the command-line interface for Passport Unlocker for Linux.
It discovers candidate USB drives and delegates privileged status or unlock
operations to a restricted helper through Polkit.
.PP
The application is unofficial and is not affiliated with or endorsed by
Western Digital.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B list
List candidate devices and their stable identifiers.
.TP
.B status
Query the security state of the selected device.
.TP
.B unlock
Read the drive password without terminal echo, unlock the selected device,
verify its state, and request a device rescan.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --device-id " STABLE_ID"
Select the stable identifier printed by
.BR passport-unlocker " list".
.TP
.B --version
Print the program version.
.SH SECURITY
The drive password is read interactively and passed to the privileged helper
over standard input. Do not provide it in command-line arguments, environment
variables, files, or logs.
.PP
This pre-alpha version has not completed real-drive validation. Back up
important data before controlled hardware testing.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR passport-unlocker-gui (1),
.BR pkexec (1)

